@jarres
title: Karl Jarres, mayor of Duisburg, former Vice-Chancellor, and the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>'s candidate in 1925.
view-if: jarres_unlock_pres
subtitle: Second times a charm.
on-arrival: reactionary_candidate_1932_count_2 -= 1
face-image: img/portraits/jarres.jpg
max-visits: 1
go-to: reactionary_candidates if reactionary_candidate_1932_count_2 > 0

Karl Jarres, having been compelled to withdraw his candidacy in 1925 in favor of Hindenburg, has once again entered the race. While not an overtly partisan figure—having remained relatively quiet in national politics in recent years—Jarres is expected to share many of the same anti-<span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> biases that Hindenburg currently harbors. Moreover, he subscribes to the "taming strategy" concerning the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>. It is imperative that we field a candidate of our own to prevent such an outcome.

His candidacy is supported by the <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>.

- @harzburg: We await the decision of the Harzburg Front.

@luther
