Hans Luther, former Chancellor of the first federal right-wing coalition and key figure in addressing the hyperinflationary crisis, is certainly not lacking in the experience required to assume the presidency of the Reich. Among his peers, he stands out as relatively open to constructive cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, though it is clear that he favors a presidential bourgeois government over continued <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> participation in power. Despite his party affiliation, he is widely viewed as a non-partisan candidate.

His candidacy is supported by the [? if not lvp_formed: <span style="color: #C0A054;">**DVP**</span>?][? if lvp_formed: <span style="color: #FFCC00;">**LVP**</span>?]. [? if not lvp_formed: He is also nominally supported by the <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**[+ ddp_name +]**</span>. ?]

- @harzburg: We await the decision of the Harzburg Front.

@gessler
title: Otto Gessler, controversial former Defense Minister and former <span style="color: #D3C24D;">**DDP**</span> member.
