Konrad Adenauer, a staunch advocate of the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>'s strategy to "leave the tower" and open itself to Protestant support, has decided to run for the presidency after achieving that very aim. Still relatively inexperienced in national politics, the Mayor is known for his strong anti-Prussian stance—going so far as to reject a chancellorship offer in 1926 on the grounds that Stresemann was "too Prussian." Aligned with Stegerwald and situated on the party's right wing, Adenauer has expressed interest in the so-called "taming strategy" toward the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>.

His candidacy is supported by the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?].

- @harzburg: We await the decision of the Harzburg Front.

