Heinrich Brüning, a politician we know all too well, is running for the most powerful position in the Reich. He has a long history, tracing back to the Christian Trade Unions and his mentorship under Stegerwald, eventually rising to become the leader of the party's parliamentary group and its candidate for Chancellor. Despite his record of favoring austerity and deflationary policies in response to the Great Depression, he is a flexible figure—intelligent enough to recognize the dangers of the "taming strategy," and not entirely opposed to governing alongside the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>.

His candidacy is supported by the [? if z_party_name != "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>?][? if z_party_name == "CVP": <span style="color: #000000;">**CVP**</span>?].

